news.title: Nirala World to invest ₹1,000 crore in two Greater Noida mixed-use projects
news.para: Nirala World is set to invest ₹1,000 crore in two mixed-use projects in Greater Noida West, featuring retail, offices, and studio apartments. While expanding, the company faces challenges due to soaring land prices in Noida and Greater Noida.

news.title: Loose tiles? Here’s what’s really causing it and the adhesive that fixes it
news.para: This guide will explain everything you need to know about wall tile adhesive. You will also know about the best products for your tile needs, and how Birla White's innovative tile products can help you achieve perfect tiling results.

news.title: Smart KLAUS Multiparking solutions reducing urban congestion in Indian cities
news.para: With space becoming a premium commodity in Indian metros and semi-urban areas, multi-parking systems can ease infrastructure strain, opined experts at a panel discussion organised by KLAUS Multiparking in association with The Times of India

news.title: Embassy REIT raises ₹1,550 crore of debt
news.para: The fund raise comprises ₹750 crore via Embassy REIT Series XIV NCDs, priced at a coupon of 6.97%, and a ₹800 crore term loan from a bank that is priced at a floating interest rate of 7.40% over a 15-year tenor.

news.title: UrbanVault launches two centres in Gurugram
news.para: Both the centres, housed in Paras Twin Tower, add a combined 35,000 sq ft of grade A workspace and approximately 700 seats. Per-seat pricing starts at ₹12,000.

news.title: Infra.Market secures $50 million additional funding from Mars Growth Capital
news.para: This is Infra.Market's second fund raising for the year. It had raised approximately $125 million in series D financing round earlier this year.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace Developers to acquire Shreyas Stones for ₹199 crore
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers would be acquiring 10,000 equity shares having face value of ₹10 each at a premium of ₹198,990 each aggregating to ₹199 crore.

news.title: Fifty farmhouses, walls built in protected Aravalis to face bulldozers this week
news.para: Fifty illegally built farmhouses — identified in a survey earlier this year — will be demolished, forest department officials said on Thursday.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government will build permanent homes for poor: Housing minister
news.para: Parthasarathy reviewed the current situation in the layouts and addressed meetings held within the layouts. He emphasized that the previous govt's lack of proper planning had caused problems and that the current govt would rectify those shortcomings and construct quality houses for the poor.

news.title: Pasarwadi villagers get two acres to build new homes in Malin
news.para: This hamlet on the edge of a hill experienced soil cracks last year raising concerns about another landslide. Its residents were anxious after the one in 2014 claimed 151 lives.

news.title: Allahabad HC quashes Greater Noida authority's order to cancel plots
news.para: The twin verdicts, delivered earlier this month by Justice Prakash Padia, restored the allotments and brought relief to the realtors, Elevator Properties and Kinetic Buildtech.

news.title: Over 3,000 residents get e-khata at Bengaluru mega mela
news.para: Bengaluru development minister DK Shivakumar inaugurated the door-to-door distribution drive by handing over draft e-khatas to local households.

news.title: Welspun bids the most for Lavasa Corporation; Lodha Developers, Jindal Steel and Power Group in fray, too
news.para: Lavasa Corporation, India's first private hill town project, is up for sale again. Creditors aim to recover their dues. Six takeover bids have been submitted, ranging from ₹500 crore to ₹850 crore. Welspun Group placed the highest bid. Other bidders include Ashdan, Pride Purple, Macrotech Developers, DB Corp subsidiary Valor, Jindal Steel and Power Group, and Yogayatan Group.

news.title: Colliers India eyes ₹1,100 crore order book in 2025 amid strong leasing pipeline, sectoral resilience
news.para: Sankey Prasad, chairman and managing director in an exclusive interview with ETRealty said that the company remains bullish on India's commercial real estate sector, citing strong fundamentals and continued demand despite global headwinds.

news.title: Hiranandani Group targets 15–20% growth in FY26; to launch new township in Alibaug
news.para: Niranjan Hiranandani, chairman of Hiranandani Group said that they will launch a 225-acre hospitality-focused township project in Alibaug by September 2025, featuring villas, plots, serviced apartments, water sports, and multiple hotels.

news.title: Dharavi redevelopment project plans to house India’s next prime business district
news.para: Dharavi's redevelopment will feature a commercial business district. This aims to attract diverse companies. The district includes offices, retail spaces, and hotels. It will boost Dharavi's economy and fund the project. The project will rehabilitate residents and businesses. Integration with transport will enhance the commercial hub. This could transform Dharavi into a mixed-use urban precinct.

news.title: Vadodara-based builder ordered to refund flat buyer's money for delay in possession
news.para: The complainants, represented by advocate Akhil Dave, stated that they booked a flat in the developer's Vadodara project in 2012, with possession promised by April 2016 under the terms of the agreement.

news.title: Every house in Indore to have digital address; pilot project launched
news.para: The project involves the installation of special digital plates with unique QR codes outside every house in Indore, the officials said on Sunday.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 43 acres land in Panipat
news.para: This project will contain approximately 1.02 million sq ft of plotted residential development and has a revenue potential in excess of ₹1,250 crore.

news.title: Only 30% of MahaRERA recovery warrants executed; ₹527 crore still to be recovered
news.para: The slow progress contradicts revenue minister Chandrakant Bawankule's assurance during the state budget session, where he emphasised speedy execution of MahaRERA's recovery warrant orders and clearing the backlog within three months.
